<item>
            <title>[SPARK-5412] Cannot bind Master to a specific hostname as per the documentation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5412</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Documentation on &lt;a href=&quot;http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/spark-standalone.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/spark-standalone.html&lt;/a&gt; indicates:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can start a standalone master server by executing:&lt;br/&gt;
./sbin/start-master.sh&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
the following configuration options can be passed to the master and worker:&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
-h HOST, --host HOST	Hostname to listen on&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&amp;#45;h&quot; or &quot;--host&quot; parameter actually doesn&apos;t work with the start-master.sh script. Instead, one has to set the &quot;SPARK_MASTER_IP&quot; variable prior to executing the script.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either the script or the documentation should be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
